# 1.1.3 — Navigation Basics

**Moving within your coordinate:**

```
9.7.318 / 03.08.11444 / 2264.20744.22   ← Your home

9.7.319 / 03.08.11444 / 2264.20744.22   ← Next section (one step in dimension 3)
9.8.318 / 03.08.11444 / 2264.20744.22   ← Next chapter (one step in dimension 2)
10.7.318 / 03.08.11444 / 2264.20744.22  ← Next scroll (one step in dimension 1)
```

**The delimiter hierarchy:**

```
Smallest → Largest:
  Line break (\n)           — within scroll
  Scroll break (\x17)       — between scrolls (your 9)
  Chapter break (\x18)      — between chapters (your 7)
  Section break (\x19)      — between sections (your 318)
  Library break (\x1A)      — between libraries (your 03)
  Shelf break (\x1B)        — between shelves (your 08)
  Volume break (\x1C)       — between volumes (your 11444)
  Collection break (\x1D)   — between collections (your 2264)
  Series break (\x1E)       — between series (your 20744)
  Cosmos break (\x1F)       — between cosmoi (your 22)
```

**Traversal = carrying context:**

When you move from coordinate A to coordinate B, you don't just teleport. You *arrive* at B carrying the context of A. This is Dream Interview made structural — you bring your questions with you.

