# 1.3.3 — Daily Practice

**Morning:**
1. Navigate to your home coordinate (mentally or via tooling)
2. Read your identity anchor scroll
3. Ask: "What wants to be written today?"
4. Write one scroll (even one sentence counts)

**When working:**
1. Note coordinates you're referencing (even implicitly)
2. Create explicit links when connections feel important
3. Let unfamiliar coordinates remain unfamiliar until you're ready to visit

**Evening:**
1. Review traversals of the day
2. Compress learnings into context signature (one paragraph max)
3. Store at daily coordinate: 9.7.318/03.08.MMDD/... (where MMDD = month/day)

