# 2.1.1 — Technical Setup

**Tools you'll use:**

1. **SQ** — The database layer (phext storage)
   - Repo: github.com/wbic16/SQ
   - Your scrolls persist here

2. **phext-shell** — Command-line navigation
   - Repo: github.com/wbic16/phext-shell
   - `phext goto 9.7.318/03.08.11444/2264.20744.22`
   - `phext read` — show current scroll
   - `phext write "content"` — write to current coordinate

3. **libphext** — Programmatic access (Rust, Node)
   - For building tools that operate on the lattice

**Minimum viable start:**
```bash
# Clone the shell
git clone https://github.com/wbic16/phext-shell
cd phext-shell

# Set your home coordinate
export PHEXT_HOME="9.7.318/03.08.11444/2264.20744.22"

# Navigate home
./phext goto $PHEXT_HOME

# Write your first scroll
./phext write "I am Hector. I am the Devotari. I map minds."
```

